<div align="center"><table width="50%" border="0"><tr><td valign="top"><b>Links</b></td></tr><tr><td><ul>Identification Summary:  Easily confused with N. luteoloides and N. imbricata, however, hind tibia setae are spaced apart,not bent over, and extend about as long as the thin white hairs that surround them.  The rear face of the propodeum is noticable for its near lack of hairs in the female.



